Third-party names, marks, and palette attributions
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This skill is a companion to Anthropic's "theme-factory" skill
(https://github.com/anthropics/skills/tree/main/theme-factory) and follows its
theme file format. It does not include or modify theme-factory's files.

The theme palettes in this pack are provided as a DESIGN REFERENCE only. Several
categories reference third-party names that are the trademarks or property of
their respective owners. Inclusion here does not imply affiliation with, or
endorsement by, any of these owners.

- Aesthetic palettes (Earthy, Feminine, Coastal, Bold, Boho, Vintage, Luxury)
  are adapted from publicly published color collections by The Brand Alchemists
  and Steph Corrigan Design.

- "Iconic Brands" reproduces publicly documented brand colors (e.g. Facebook,
  Instagram, X/Twitter, Tesla, McDonald's, Nike, Spotify, Google, Netflix,
  Coca-Cola, Slack, Starbucks, Amazon, Airbnb). All brand names and colors are
  the property of their respective owners.

- The developer/editor/terminal categories use the published color
  specifications of community themes (e.g. Dracula, Nord, Gruvbox, Tokyo Night,
  Catppuccin, Solarized, Monokai, One Dark, Night Owl, GitHub, Rosé Pine,
  Everforest, Synthwave '84, Cobalt2, Shades of Purple, Spaceduck, Horizon).
  The Obsidian-native themes (Things, Minimal, Blue Topaz, Primary, AnuPpuccin)
  are approximations of each theme's signature look. All theme names belong to
  their respective authors.

- "Master Painters" and "Directors & Cinematographers" palettes are original
  color selections DERIVED from each artist's or filmmaker's iconic work. Most
  source works are in the public domain. These are evocations for design use,
  not reproductions, and the artists' names belong to their respective estates
  or owners.

Theme names, color-role assignments, font pairings, and usage guidance in this
pack were authored by the maintainer.
